resources.string:
If A is an m x n matrix and B is an n x p matrix, then

• AB is defined whose size is m x p;
• BA may not be defined (if p ≠ m);
• If BA is defined, BA will be n x n and AB will be m x m and if m ≠ n, AB and BA are of different sizes; and
• If BA and AB are of the same size, they may be unequal.
